2500|$|She {{would also}} later state that these events delayed her career by about ten years, as [...] "it seemed <b>like</b> <b>an</b> <b>eternity</b> in which I was {{the punch line}} to every late-night {{monologue}} ... Joan Rivers, whom I adored and met on The Tonight Show during my reign, was particularly relentless. Just when I figured she'd exhausted every possible Vanessa Williams joke, she'd have a whole new slew of them." [...] Williams would also later tell of one audition that she had during the late 1980s for a theatrical role. She was denied the role, however, because [...] "the wife of lyricist Ira Gershwin decreed: 'Over my dead body will that whore be in my show.' [...] " [...] In addition, her parents experienced [...] "an incredible amount of shame and humiliation" [...] and were equally the subject of harassment at the time.|$|E
